<subSubSection id="46F06573112D724DF8A10FAF874E22F9" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="231" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0E5536F8112D724DF8A10FAF874E22F9" blockId="29.[151,1437,1965,2028]" lastBlockId="30.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="231" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112D724EF8A10FAF841F2493" bold="true" box="[151,267,1965,1991]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112D724EF9270FAF84E72493" baseAuthorityName="Adams" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[273,499,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inderena">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112D724EF9270FAF84E72493" box="[273,499,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">Manerebia inderena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has so far been considered as a widely distributed polytypic species. Our preliminary molecular results suggest that at least some of its subspecies should be raised to specific status. The most outstanding case is 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112E724DF942089586B023E5" authority="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006" authorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott" authorityYear="2006" box="[372,932,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="inderena" subSpecies="antioquiana">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DF9420895849F23E4" box="[372,395,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DF9AC0895879F23E4" box="[410,651,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">inderena antioquiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7B4B09112E724DFAA5089586B023E5" author="Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. &amp; Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L." box="[659,932,151,177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" pagination="37 - 79" refId="ref22357" refString="Pyrcz, T. W., Willmott, K. R., Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L. (2006) A review of the genus Manerebia Staudinger (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae: Satyrinae) in the northern Andes. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera, 39, 37 - 79." type="journal article" year="2006">Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the northern portion of the Colombian Central Cordillera, which is highly divergent genetically from other subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112E724DFC0C08B981D72381" baseAuthorityName="Adams" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[1082,1219,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inderena">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFC0C08B981452380" box="[1082,1105,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFC5608B981D72381" box="[1120,1219,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">inderena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Also, 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112E724DFD2208B984E523AD" authority="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006" authorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="inderena" subSpecies="clara">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFD2208B9803F2380" box="[1300,1323,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFD0C08B985C623AD" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">inderena clara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7B4B09112E724DF8ED08DD84E523AD" author="Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. &amp; Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L." box="[219,497,223,249]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" pagination="37 - 79" refId="ref22357" refString="Pyrcz, T. W., Willmott, K. R., Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L. (2006) A review of the genus Manerebia Staudinger (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae: Satyrinae) in the northern Andes. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera, 39, 37 - 79." type="journal article" year="2006">Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the eastern Andean slopes in central 
<collectingCountry id="76FD7668112E724DFBD708DD815423AD" box="[993,1088,223,249]" name="Ecuador" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, does not segregate with other subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112E724DF90D090184DE2249" baseAuthorityName="Adams" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[315,458,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inderena">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DF90D090184462248" box="[315,338,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DF952090184DE2249" box="[356,458,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">inderena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DF9FC090184DA2249" box="[458,462,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">.</emphasis>
Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112E724DFA450901814D2249" authority="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006" authorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott" authorityYear="2006" box="[627,1113,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="inderena" subSpecies="fina">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFA450901879E2248" box="[627,650,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFAAA090186212249" box="[668,821,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">inderena fina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7B4B09112E724DFB090901814D2249" author="Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. &amp; Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L." box="[831,1113,259,285]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" pagination="37 - 79" refId="ref22357" refString="Pyrcz, T. W., Willmott, K. R., Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L. (2006) A review of the genus Manerebia Staudinger (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae: Satyrinae) in the northern Andes. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera, 39, 37 - 79." type="journal article" year="2006">Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the western slopes in 
<collectingCountry id="76FD7668112E724DF8A1092585E22215" box="[151,246,295,321]" name="Ecuador" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, unexpectedly forms a highly supported clade with 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112E724DFB76092581622215" authority="Brown, 1944" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="1944" box="[832,1142,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interrupta">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFB76092586432214" box="[832,855,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFB50092586CC2214" box="[870,984,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">interrupta</emphasis>
Brown, 1944
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112E724DFC84092584752231" authority="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006" authorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="golondrina">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFC84092581DD2214" box="[1202,1225,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DFCEE092580402215" box="[1240,1364,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">golondrina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7B4B09112E724DFD6A092584752231" author="Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. &amp; Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L." pageId="30" pageNumber="231" pagination="37 - 79" refId="ref22357" refString="Pyrcz, T. W., Willmott, K. R., Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L. (2006) A review of the genus Manerebia Staudinger (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae: Satyrinae) in the northern Andes. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera, 39, 37 - 79." type="journal article" year="2006">Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B112E724DF9F0094986AE2231" authority="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006" authorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott" authorityYear="2006" box="[454,954,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="inderena" subSpecies="mirena">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DF9F0094984C92230" box="[454,477,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA112E724DF9DA094987B72230" box="[492,675,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">inderena mirena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7B4B09112E724DFA9C094986AE2231" author="Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. &amp; Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L." box="[682,954,331,357]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" pagination="37 - 79" refId="ref22357" refString="Pyrcz, T. W., Willmott, K. R., Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Viloria, A. L. (2006) A review of the genus Manerebia Staudinger (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae: Satyrinae) in the northern Andes. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera, 39, 37 - 79." type="journal article" year="2006">Pyrcz &amp; Willmott, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, in south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="76FD7668112E724DFC48094981CF2231" box="[1150,1243,331,357]" name="Ecuador" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
is most probably a complex of at least two cryptic species, and further work using a more comprehensive set of samples is underway to clarify the taxonomy of this complex.
</paragraph>
